The paper deals with the analysis of source coding, which is a fundamental problem in information theory and falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of R\'{e}nyi entropy, which is a generalization of Shannon entropy, suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability). The analysis of the error exponent and strong converse exponent suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of various techniques such as one-shot bounds and moments of type class enumerator method suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
